        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>mordrakken</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Nope, I'm not being rooted. Most of these mobs don't rampage, or anything like that. I can be in melee range or out. They can be slowed or not slowed. I can have done 4k in damage or just a tap if it's early in the fight. I can have dots running or have none. I'm not standing up and being hit, I'm staying down, and still being hit. There is no failure message, for either me or my group. This isn't a one time occurance that I may have missed in spam, this is a behavior that I have experienced time and time again. Hell, if rooted, they'll beat on a melee, then when root breaks they'll come over and hit me while I'm still feigned (with no falls down message).</P><P>The only reason being in melee range matters for the purposes of this is that they'll be more likely to hit me if I'm close -- and they're hitting me, of course, else I wouldn't notice it. The rock golems I mentioned, for instance are usually ST'd or rooted by me for crowd control. I feign to try to make them go for a tank when they break the root or mez, but even on a success, the mob still comes for me. I'm never within melee range for that. I'm usually about half casting range  or so to give the melee a chance to hold aggro. And no, it doesn't only happen when a mob comes off mez (which was also something I thought about -- ie: the mob holding a target while mezzed where it normally would have had to give it up), so that's out too.</P><P>As I said, go to the hole or the bats in ME, take a few friends. Try it. Try it solo. Try it grouped. Try it with a pet. Try it without. If it never happens to you, then make the best of it: You'll never have a problem surviving anything. But I and the friends I group with daily are well aware that it can, and does, happen. We just call that the mobs (or mob type -- as I said before, not all mobs in a certain zone share the capability) see through feign as soon as it happens and I stay in low aggro mode for the rest of the fighting there or against those mobs.</P><P>Some necros have experienced this, some haven't. It could be that it doesn't happen when solo as often, it could be that it is a bug. It could be completely intentional. It could be many things -- lord knows feign has had problems before (ask any monk, they'll tell you about entire months when things would just see through feign for no reason -- check the patch archives on castersrealm for the resolutions to same). It may be that it is a bug in the hate list or target selection code that allows you to remain a target for the mob when you shouldn't normally be.</P><P>It would be interesting to have a poll to see what percentage of necromancers (or SKs, or even monks) have experienced this. I think I'll go peruse the monk boards.</P><P><BR> </font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>mordrakken</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> But one of the pages commenting on FD on monkly-business.</P><P><a href="http://monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=164" target="_blank">http://monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=164</a></P><P>To quote a few relevant portions:</P><P>Q: Are there any known bugs in Feign Death?</P><P>A: There are a few known bugs, all of which are notorious for being hard to repeat and hard to fix. Sometimes, when using the first person view, attempting to immediately stand up after feigning will cause you to be unable to move. Sitting, then standing again will clear this, but be very careful because even green mobs will aggro on you if you sit. When pulling higher-level creatures I would recommend using a third-person view anyway, so practice using both the view and the skills early. There is also a very annoying bug which causes FD to fail with no messages sometimes when there are multiple characters on a mob's aggro list(almost all the time during grouping/raiding). This is still being researched by Verant staff, and they seem to have reduced its occurrence (though it's not been totally fixed yet). </P><P>Also of note:</P><P>Q: What breaks a successful Feign?</P><P>A: Two things will break a sucessful feign: (1) getting hit by any spell except a dispell, beneficial or harmful, including AEs, and (2) moving. There are lots of things that could make you move while FD -- steep slopes, accidentally right-clicking on a corpse (and thereby looting it) when you're trying to con a mob, or finishing a bandage all count as movement.</P><P>And yet another (the edit):</P><P>Q: What's the FD bug, and what can I do to fix it?</P><P>A: "The FD bug" that people refer to is the one where you hit the FD key, fall over, don't get any of the various failure messages, but you still get beaten on like a madman. Some things you can do to fix it --</P><P>1. Make sure that autoattack is off when you hit FD. Make sure autoattack has been off long enough to catch up to your lag; that means waiting at least 3 seconds, if you're on a dialup or under raid lag.</P><P>2. Move around a bit before you FD (unless you habitually get the "you have moved and are no longer feigning death" message). Most people jump back.</P><P>3. Make sure that the failure wasn't caused by something more mundane, like a message you missed due to spam or lag.</P><P>Also, guides usually don't give rezzes for deaths due to "The FD Bug", since it's not a recognized one. Also, VI's said that they've tried to fix this one, and its occurrence has been greatly reduced since they've said it.</P><P>Edited by - mordrakken on 06/18/2002  17:22:17</font></td>
